 I need AC I pop on a cleric breastplate or a BEBP.  <P>When I need wisdom I pop on a runed mithril tunic.<P>The Gi is 14 ac and some +mana.<P>I see people wearing the Gi for "fashion" I guess when they have not hit 200 mana.  Just my opinion but they would be better served by getting a mixed AC/wisdom item like the BS Tunic or go for Wis or AC appropriately.  Seems weird to wear a key piece (chest slot) that is not giving you the maximum benefit from the slot.  *shrug*<P>I worry more about my effectivness than fashion.  Must be because I'm a dwarf (grin).  Funny, the only folks I've ever seen in the robes are high elves.  Explains a lot.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Duvessa Sorenthaine</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Personally, I wear the robes because they look nice, the additional hitpoints and mana are sometimes a saving grace, and it weighs considerably less than the chestplate of the constant that I have.<P>Let's face it, when you're a dark elf your banking/selling ports are a little limited, especially while hunting around Omen so you do what you can to get around encumberance restrictions.<P>As for using the robes as a sign of a "bad" cleric? A stereotype.<P>------------------<BR>Duvessa Sorenthaine<BR>Priestess of Innoruuk</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Sentia</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Where does the Robe come from anyways?</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">tfboc</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial"> <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>Originally posted by Sentia:<BR><B>Where does the Robe come from anyways?</B><HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>The Mines of Nurga. It's an upper mid-level dungeon on Kunark that can be entered from the Frontier Mountains. Drops of various Burnyai there.<BR><P>------------------<BR>Qweeby, Ogre Warrior<BR>Savnurahs, Dark Elf Cleric<BR>Officer of The Hidden<BR>The Rathe</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Veloran</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I'm with Ofbac on this one.<P>How is the Robe a fashionable item? I'm proud of the fact that I am a Cleric. It's funny, clerics use to complain about looking like a druid, but now think it's cool to like like a caster? I personally don't care to blend in and look like a caster. When I want fashion, I rotate my chestpiece from Cleric Gold, to Mithril Blue to Black Enam, and hopefully one day to Purple planar. <P>------------------<BR>Veloran Triumphante<BR>50th High Cleric of Tunare<BR>Quellious</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Aosinator</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Veloran,<P>Choosing to look like a druid is one thing, being "forced" to look like a druid is quite another.  For a long time, there really weren't all that many options to a cleric, who wanted to maximize their wisdom.  They had to run around with various pieces of armor that looked like leather.<P>I guess fashion isn't just about changing the tint of your your clothes (in your case your breastplate), and is more about looking "unique"?  I don't know the answer to this one, but I know that fashion isn't wearing 3 identical breastplates with different colors.  =P  It's more about going for a new look, or doing something that no one else has done before.<P>I have several distinct outfits depending on the situation and my mood.  >=)  If I want to impersonate a wizard, I wield my Staff of Forbidden Rites, put on my Efreeti boots, sebilite scale gloves (passes quite nicely for carmine gloves), and don my Robe of Seekers.  Then I walk around emoting <Starts to cast Ice Comet>, then say BOOM!  I do it in jest and in fun, to entertain myself and those around me.  Plus, it's nice to look different every now and then.<P>P.S. All of the above works for an enchanter as well except swap the Robe for a Gi, the SoFR for a primsatic shield and a mug, then cast Hammer of Unswerving Faith on something.  You'll get tells for clarity soon nuff.   <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/wink.gif">  (Heck I used to get tells for clarity with my Robe of Seekers on!)<P>------------------<BR>-Aosinator Lightbringer<BR>-Devout Follower of Mithaniel Marr<BR>-The Rathe</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Ninda</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Don't understand the need for fashion?  You must be a DORF!  EEEEEEEk.<P>Just as a side note:  I've never seen a dorf in this robe, and actually I think either a) its class restricted so dorfs can't wear them, or b) dorfs don't get the cool graphic.<P>Either way, would any self respecting dorf be caught in a dress?  ;=)  High elf female clerics, now there's fashion! </FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Dalur - Veeshan</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">You are correct in a sense.  Verant was too lazy to create a robe graphic for halflings and for dwarves (not dorfs) so we won't be able to wear any robes. <P>------------------<BR>Dalur Stouthealer<BR>53rd Dwarven Vicar<BR>Veeshan Server</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">vfelia</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Fashion has nothing to do with fighting.. For the most part.. <P> When i'm running around.. maybe soloing, or what not.. I wear my robes(especially when I'm medding).. if I really need that extra few mana from the few points of wis or other bonus's.. I'll throw my Tunic on, but really<P> I'm sick of looking like i'm 4th level just to get my 200 wis.. So I like throwing on a robe.. and people ask me all the time what class I am, or what is the robe.. and that is jus